	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Greetings All - <BR>
<BR>
I am a Druid Halfling in my 19th season.  I've managed to combine melee and casting quite effectively.  I normally root or snare, then cast a DoT spell, ignite (whirling wind if the target is a caster - it interupts their spells), then depending on where their health is I either recast the sequence or I go ahead and begin fighting.  I have managed to get my skills up and with buffs such as skin like rock, strength, and firefist I manage to kill those that con black or blue to me with melee.  I normally hit for anywhere between 1-14 though with the weapon I have (1H Blunt) some kind of shards occasionally hit them (velium???).  This will work better once I have the level for it to be more effective.  I believe the DMG is 8 and attack delay in the 30's.  It works for me.  I have kept my experience in Offense and Defense maxed for my level by always joining in the fight when grouped after me manna is low.  I'm a newbie so don't take my word for it - but it's been working great for the last 19 levels!<BR>
<BR>
Remember - be kind to those around you and your kindness will be repaid later!<BR>
<BR>
Brigitt
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
