	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just a few comments:<BR>
Druids are very bad at melee, yes, but that doesn't mean it should be neglected completely. I find it very convenient at times to be able to smash things with my club. The most important function of your weapon will still be to add stats anyway. Which brings me to choice of weapons type: DO NOT USE 2HB WEAPONS. 1HS and 1HB are both ok, with more good intermediate weapons in 1hb. The reason for never using 2HB? If you choose to wield a weapon you will still want the bonus adds from the off hand. Assuming you get a testament of vanear (quest, cost time plus about 10 pp) your off hand yields 10 wisdom 10 mana, and together with a velium etched mace mace (cost around 300 pp nowadays on Fennin Ro), that would equal a 2HB weapon with 7 damage 22 delay 3 str, 13 wisdom 10 mana. Try to find one like that for reasonable money and I'm proved wrong (ok ignore the melee stats, not that important anyway, the druid will never be a good meleer anyway). <BR>
Another problem with 2HB is that the delays are normally rather long, making it a hard skill to learn, especially since we don't get to melee that much at higher levels... <BR>
If you ever get to doing your epic, you might want to have some basic skill in 1HS as well... at least if you ever want to hit something with it...  Well that's about all the wisdom I have to pass on I believe. And oh yes, wear sunscreen.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
